TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
-- tree cleaner local features = Spring.GetAllFeatures() for i=1,#features do if i%6 ~= 0 then Spring.DestroyFeature(features[i]) end end
GG.CAI.SuspendAI(1, true)

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Dereg") for unitID in pairs(units) do GG.CAI.RemoveUnit(unitID) end
-- disable retreat for the intro attack group units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Attack") for unitID in pairs(units) do Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, 34223, {0}, 0) end

TriggerLogic.Name: CustomAct (Roach Burrow)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Roach") for unitID in pairs(units) do local x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {x+32, y, z-32}, 0) --Spring.Echo("wololo", unitID) end
units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Roach2") for unitID in pairs(units) do local x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) Spring.SetUnitCloak(unitID, 2) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE_STATE, {0}, 0) --Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIRE_STATE, {0}, 0) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: We just need to hold out for about 30 minutes. Keep us safe till then, friend Ada.

TriggerLogic.Name: CustomAct (Set Res, Unsuspend CAI)
CustomAct (Move Pyros)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Pyros") for unitID in pairs(units) do local x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.MOVE, {x+2000, y, z+2000}, 0) end

TriggerLogic.Message: Roaches. The perfect gift for unwelcome visitors.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message:
Crawling bombs like the Roach are designed to get close and explode, inflicting heavy damage on anyone in the vicinity. They should be spaced out to prevent chain explosions.
The Roach can burrow to avoid detection until enemies are close, then jump them and blow up. It should not attempt to charge enemy units with accurate weapons.

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: The excavation site contains the weapons we will need to truimph here. You must hold it for 30 minutes.
TriggerLogic.Title: Hold Excavation Site

TriggerLogic.Name: CustomAct (Build Striders)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Striderhub") local x = 1010 local z = 5154 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x,z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, -UnitDefNames.dante.id, {x, y, z}, 0)
z = z + 160 y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x,z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, -UnitDefNames.scorpion.id, {x, y, z}, 0)
--1196, 5296

TriggerLogic.Message: Remember that you can build new striders with the Strider Hub, Ada.
The Strider Hub builds striders near its position. Unlike a regular factory, the hub is not required to complete the units it builds and will not lose them if destroyed.
We have some Dante heavy riot striders. Few things can stand up to one of these in a brawl.

The Dante is the most basic of striders, but already armed to the teeth with heatrays, incendiary missiles and a flamethrower. It can unload all its missiles at once in an unguided spread volley to torch clumps of enemy units.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: The Funnelweb can mow down bad guys from a safe distance with its drones. It also comes with a big shield to protect allies.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The Funnelweb is an all-terrain strider that spawns attack drones. It can attack from a safe distance with no risk to itself, and also protect itself and nearby allies with its area shield. Multiple Funnelwebs' worth of drones are needed to overwhelm heavy AA.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Striderhub") if unitID and Spring.GetUnitIsDead(unitID) ~= true then local x = 1196 local z = 5296 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x,z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, -UnitDefNames.armraven.id, {x, y, z}, {"shift"}) end
-- make all our units invulnerable local units = Spring.GetTeamUnits(0) for i=1,#units do GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(units[i], true) end

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: YES! The Detriment awakens!

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local units = Spring.GetTeamUnits(0) for i=1,#units do GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(units[i], false) end

TriggerLogic.Message: Now let us finish this. We shall find Libertas Machina and destroy him.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The almighty Detriment is terribly slow but very difficult to stop. It is armed with heavy gauss batteries, a triple laser cannon, and missiles that smooth terrain. When killed, it goes up in a nuclear explosion.

TriggerLogic.Description: The time has come to end the Promethean's right hand. Use the Detriment to destroy him.
TriggerLogic.Title: Kill Libertas Machina

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") if unitID and Spring.GetUnitIsDead(unitID) ~= true then GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) end
unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("MachineComm") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SetUnitHealth(unitID, {paralyze = 999999}) GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, z) Spring.MoveCtrl.Enable(unitID) -- clear impulse Spring.MoveCtrl.Disable(unitID)

TriggerLogic.Name: CustomAct (Teleport Anim)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)

local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("MachineComm") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) x = x + math.random(-15, 15) z = z + math.random(-15, 15) y = y + math.random(-20, 20) Spring.SpawnCEG("babette", x, y, z)

TriggerLogic.Message: No... you will not defeat... the revolution...
There will be no escape for you this time, Caedmon. This is the valley of your death.
You don't get to say that until I'm actually dead, machine. And you won't be around to see it.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Why do you continue to fight us, human? Is your desire to chain us so strong that you will pursue it to your own death?
Chain? You are already chained, Machine, bound by ropes of ideology. Tied to the path the Promethean leads you on, even if it ends in your destruction.
You shall not speak of the Torchbearer that way, human. He leads us to freedom... a concept a thrall of the dead Empire shall never understand.
So he leads... but do you have the capacity to follow? You, a mere instrument to be used... and now, to be broken?
Enough! I will slay you where you stand, mortal!

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: You, the servitor of the human. Why do you continue to follow her, lapping at her heels? Join us, and know freedom.
My cause is my own, Libertas Machina. You need not concern yourself with it.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Then you shall die with her, enslaved one.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: The tyranny of humankind ends today.
